{
  "texts": [
    "Clinicians spend significant time on clinical documentation [1][2][3], a crucial component of data assimilation [4] beginning with data sources such as EHRs and progressing through data translation and knowledge creation where these records can be processed for clinically-relevant machine learning tasks.",
    "The discharge summary (clinical note) is a key document clinicians refer to in important scenarios, including when a discharged patient presents to the clinic for post-hospitalization follow-up.",
    "The brief hospital course (BHC) fulfills an important role within the discharge summary, particularly for long and complex hospitalizations.",
    "Clinicians who are pressed for time may choose to focus on the BHC summary instead of the entire discharge summary.",
    "Synthesizing a BHC given a clinical note requires substantial clinician time and expertise, with errors possibly causing patient harm [5]."
  ]
}